HRSA training to respond to bioterror events content skip header and navigation H R S A News Brief http www hhs gov U S Department of Health Human Services Health Resources and Services Administration HRSA NEWS ROOM http newsroom hrsa gov http newsroom hrsa gov May 13 2003 Contact HRSA Press Office 301 443 3376 HRSA Funds Available to Train Health Professionals to Respond to Bioterror Events HHS Health Resources and Services Administration announced in the May 5 http www access gpo gov nara index html Federal Register the availability of 26 million in FY 2003 to support a new two year program to train the health care workforce to respond to bioterrorism and other public health emergencies Applications for funds are due by June 30 awards will be announced in late September Under the Bioterrorism Training and Curriculum Development Program funds will be awarded to provide continuing education and training for practicing health care providers and to enhance curricula in health professions schools The goal of the program is to develop a health care workforce that can recognize indications of a terrorist event treat the acute care needs of patients arising from such an event including pediatric and other vulnerable populations participate in a coordinated multidisciplinary response to terrorist events and other public health emergencies and rapidly and effectively alert the public health system of such an event As many as 38 000 health care professionals will be trained annually Trainees may include health care providers serving in public and private hospitals community health centers migrant health centers Federally Qualified Health Centers National Health Service Corps sites and private and group practice Awards will be in the form of cooperative agreements to eligible entities to fund continuing education for providers and curricular enhancement in health professions schools HRSA expects to award up to 37 cooperative agreements of varying amounts Application materials are available at http bhpr hrsa gov grants applications 03bioterror htm http bhpr hrsa gov grants applications 03bioterror htm Hard copies may be obtained from the HRSA Grants Application Center Grants Management Office 901 Russell Ave Suite 450 Gaithersburg Md 20879 phone 877 477 2123 or fax at 877 477 2345 Refer to program announcement number HRSA 03 099 To help prepare potential applicants HRSA will conduct technical assistance workshops in the following sites and dates Chicago May 13 San Francisco May 15 Boston May 21 Dallas May 23 Washington D C May 28 Denver May 30 and Atlanta June 3 Attendance is voluntary and at the expense of the participant and registration is required On line registration is available at http meetings z techcorp com cmt http meetings z techcorp com cmt For more information on the Bioterrorism Training and Curriculum Development Program contact Lynn Wegman at 301 443 1648 fax 301 443 0157 or email mailto lwegman hrsa gov lwegman hrsa gov Go to http newsroom hrsa gov H R S A News Room HRSA News Room http www hrsa gov H R S A HRSA http www hhs gov H H S HHS http www hrsa gov 508access htm Accessibility http www hhs gov Privacy html Privacy http www hhs gov Disclaimer html Disclaimers http newsroom hrsa gov search default htm Search http answers hrsa gov cgi bin hrsa cfg php enduser std alp php Questions 
